   He always had the upper hand.

36:49.000 --> 36:52.520
After the fire
that killed my family,

36:52.520 --> 36:56.040
George and I always
shared the same room,

36:56.040 --> 36:58.640
     the shame bed for a year.

36:58.640 --> 37:01.520
We were always in trouble together.

37:01.520 --> 37:05.080
Kids need the opportunity to mess
up. We tell them to learn from us

37:05.080 --> 37:06.920
but they can't, they have
to make their own mistakes.

37:06.920 --> 37:09.800
 My conscience started to emerge.

37:09.800 --> 37:13.240
I always had a streak
of morality in me.

37:13.240 --> 37:17.080
Father McCabe put a fire to it,
but it never happened to George so

37:17.080 --> 37:21.080
I had to decide between what my sense
of right was and my blood brother.

37:24.120 --> 37:26.480
       And he felt betrayed.

37:26.480 --> 37:28.680
         I love that guy,

37:28.680 --> 37:32.120
and I hurt him. I'd like to
make things up with him but I

37:32.120 --> 37:33.800
don't suppose it would make
any difference, would it?

37:33.800 --> 37:37.560
Marcy and I are finally beginning
to understand one another.

37:37.560 --> 37:41.000
It took a real crisis and
several pounds of chocolate but,

37:41.000 --> 37:45.000
next time you see your friend,
tell him how you feel.

37:50.920 --> 37:53.240
          Glad he's gone.

37:53.240 --> 37:56.040
With that kind of tobacco
consumption, he's not going

37:56.040 --> 37:57.880
   to see the baby's graduation.

37:57.880 --> 38:01.880
Why do men get out stogies
anyway? No one smokes any more.

38:02.160 --> 38:04.560
Did I tell you I was
going to have twins?

38:04.560 --> 38:08.560
Twice.

38:09.000 --> 38:10.680
Used to be everything was
up in the air until game day.

38:10.680 --> 38:14.680
Now with amnios and sonograms,
there's a lot less mystery.

38:15.680 --> 38:18.440
  I always wanted to be a father.

38:18.440 --> 38:20.000
And play third base for the Bo Sox...

38:20.000 --> 38:24.000
    I know my time has passed.

38:24.000 --> 38:27.920
And besides, they got bogs
for at least a generation.

38:27.920 --> 38:30.440
       My kids will be next.

38:30.440 --> 38:34.440
Teach them to keep their head down
for ground balls, hit inside curves.

38:37.400 --> 38:39.360
It's a boy, Captain Walker.

38:39.360 --> 38:41.160
It's a boy!

38:41.160 --> 38:42.000
All right!

38:42.000 --> 38:46.000
         Congratulations.

38:51.000 --> 38:55.000
   So, who do I celebrate with?

38:56.120 --> 39:00.120
      Hope Marcus isn't here.

39:04.520 --> 39:08.520
Come here.

39:29.160 --> 39:33.160
I wonder what it's like being dead.

39:49.600 --> 39:50.760
I told him not to carry a gun.

39:50.760 --> 39:52.040
I told him not to carry a gun.
Who?

39:52.040 --> 39:56.040
All of a sudden, the guy in the
liquor store is pulling a gun.

39:56.960 --> 40:00.960
Then he fires, and Henry fires.

40:02.960 --> 40:05.440
There's Henry,

40:05.440 --> 40:09.160
and he's lying in a pool of blood.

40:09.160 --> 40:13.160
Twitching, and making these noises.

40:14.680 --> 40:18.680
He was my friend.

40:30.120 --> 40:32.160
Ah, Daniel, I've been
looking all over for you.

40:32.160 --> 40:36.000
As I have for you.
How did your meeting go?

40:36.000 --> 40:37.640
Promising.
Yours?

40:37.640 --> 40:39.080
         Hopeful, I think.

40:39.080 --> 40:40.160
What's your plan?

40:40.160 --> 40:41.200
     I'm sure yours is better.

40:41.200 --> 40:42.640
No, No. You first.

40:42.640 --> 40:43.600
          I'd rather not.

40:43.600 --> 40:44.520
Me neither.

40:44.520 --> 40:45.360
               Fine.

40:45.360 --> 40:49.360
Then to hell with you.

40:56.840 --> 40:58.080
Hi.

40:58.080 --> 40:59.600
       Can I take Ryan home?

40:59.600 --> 41:01.600
Well, his lab tests are
looking better and his

41:01.600 --> 41:03.200
blood sugar has levelled out.

41:03.200 --> 41:06.200
Doesn't seem to show any adverse
effects from the insulin, so...

41:06.200 --> 41:10.200
as long as you stay close to a
family doctor, he's all yours.

41:11.560 --> 41:14.000
       In summer we used to

41:14.000 --> 41:16.360
come by this hospital
on the way home from Fenway.

41:16.360 --> 41:19.640
Exhausted from all that hollering.

41:19.640 --> 41:22.480
I felt we'd been part of something.

41:22.480 --> 41:25.320
Good days.

41:25.320 --> 41:28.880
  Friendships are rare, you know?

41:28.880 --> 41:29.880
     Never had one like ours.

41:29.880 --> 41:32.960
     Never had one like ours.
Neither have I.

41:32.960 --> 41:35.760
We ought to plan to get together
every now and then.

41:35.760 --> 41:37.040
            Old times.

41:37.040 --> 41:39.400
Yeah, sure. Sounds good to me.

41:39.400 --> 41:40.440
            I'll call.

41:40.440 --> 41:44.440
Maybe you call. Whichever.
Terrific.

41:45.240 --> 41:49.240
            Take care.

42:00.120 --> 42:02.080
Hey, Dr Fiscus, wait up.

42:02.080 --> 42:03.880
I'd like to have a word with you.

42:03.880 --> 42:06.680
Melissa and the kids,
they're doing fine.

42:06.680 --> 42:09.000
           That's nice.

42:09.000 --> 42:11.040
I am sorry I punched you yesterday.

42:11.040 --> 42:15.040
Dr Morrison told me the reason
for your stupid behaviour.

42:16.320 --> 42:17.520
            It's fine.

42:17.520 --> 42:19.120
I realise the children aren't mine.

42:19.120 --> 42:22.040
I accept reality.
Now leave me alone.

42:22.040 --> 42:26.040
Look, when we found out
we couldn't have kids, and

42:26.640 --> 42:29.960
it was my fault...
  It hits a man where he lives.

42:29.960 --> 42:33.960
it's so hard accepting someone
else father of your children.

42:36.640 --> 42:39.600
You did us an extraordinary favour.

42:39.600 --> 42:42.280
I'll be grateful to you for ever.

42:42.280 --> 42:44.720
But I can't live my life wondering
if you're standing in the dark

42:44.720 --> 42:48.360
looking through the bushes
    at the babies.

42:48.360 --> 42:52.120
I need your word you
won't ever try to see them.

42:52.120 --> 42:55.440
            I promise.

42:55.440 --> 42:59.440
Well then, come with me.

43:03.800 --> 43:05.280
Come on, Rye Crisp.

43:05.280 --> 43:08.040
Jam that baby in.

43:08.040 --> 43:11.800
Two...

43:11.800 --> 43:12.240
Hey, Mike, where you going?

43:12.240 --> 43:14.360
Hey, Mike, where you going?
Leaving the kiddy ward.

43:14.360 --> 43:15.040
Why?

43:15.040 --> 43:16.200
Why?
I don't belong here.

43:16.200 --> 43:20.200
I'm 17. I'm supposed to be in adult.

43:20.200 --> 43:22.800
Henry'll never get any older.

43:22.800 --> 43:24.440
Come on.

43:24.440 --> 43:28.120
Give yourself the old spike.

43:28.120 --> 43:29.320
Wait a minute.

43:29.320 --> 43:30.600
You can do it.

43:30.600 --> 43:31.840
It's gonna hurt!

43:31.840 --> 43:35.840
It's gonna hurt!
Gotta grow up.

43:45.000 --> 43:49.000
Look, I'll scream for you,
    all right?

44:03.440 --> 44:07.440
Push the stuff in. Ry, man!

44:09.320 --> 44:13.320
He can do this solo.

44:18.240 --> 44:20.880
Wicked!

44:20.880 --> 44:24.880
No problem!

44:32.400 --> 44:36.400
Meet Darcy Tillman.

44:38.720 --> 44:42.720
And Kyle Tillman.

44:46.360 --> 44:48.240
        They're beautiful.

44:48.240 --> 44:52.240
Wait. I'm not finished.

44:53.400 --> 44:56.600
This is CJ Tillman.

44:56.600 --> 45:00.600
           A hat-trick!

45:02.000 --> 45:05.520
   A few months ago I was shot.

45:05.520 --> 45:08.320
   Almost never opened my eyes.

45:08.320 --> 45:12.320
And when I did,
all I saw was a dead world.

45:12.920 --> 45:16.640
People discarded like trash on the
streets, friends growing bitter and

45:16.640 --> 45:18.880
       strung out on drugs.

45:18.880 --> 45:22.880
The ER overflowing and under
financial pressure to cut back.

45:23.520 --> 45:25.320
          I lost hope and

45:25.320 --> 45:29.320
became as negative as
the world around me.

45:30.800 --> 45:34.400
But I'm beginning to see I was
given a second chance at life,

45:34.400 --> 45:36.520
   so that I could participate.

45:36.520 --> 45:40.200
       To add, not subtract.

45:40.200 --> 45:44.200
  Tinker...to Evers...to Chance.

45:46.560 --> 46:24.000
               Wow!
